00:25:00,775 --> 00:25:04,438
- Ma, I'm goin' to Ned's.
- Well, don't be late.

242
00:25:04,513 --> 00:25:06,947
- Are you all right ?
- Aye.

243
00:25:15,957 --> 00:25:18,824
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

244
00:25:20,562 --> 00:25:22,996
Congratulations, Peter.

245
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:27,434
Harry.

246
00:25:35,944 --> 00:25:37,878
[ Joe ]
Harry.

247
00:25:47,088 --> 00:25:50,615
Peter Mallon's been elected
to the army council.

248
00:25:54,195 --> 00:25:57,392
I've decided I need
somebody more political.

249
00:25:59,801 --> 00:26:04,363
All operations are to be
suspended from 12:00 tomorrow.

250
00:26:05,907 --> 00:26:08,000
- Noon.
- Noon.

251
00:26:08,076 --> 00:26:10,010
Tomorrow.

252
00:26:10,078 --> 00:26:13,047
- Tomorrow.
- Why ?

253
00:26:15,417 --> 00:26:19,251
- We're close to a deal, Harry.
- Includin' the P.O.W.s ?

254
00:26:19,321 --> 00:26:21,585
Includin' the P.O.W.s.

255
00:26:23,725 --> 00:26:28,287
So what are you
offerin', Joe ? Hmm ?

256
00:26:28,363 --> 00:26:31,992
Peace, Harry. Peace.

257
00:26:33,268 --> 00:26:36,965
Peace. I'm sure
you can deliver, Joe.

258
00:26:47,315 --> 00:26:49,340
Left hand up.

259
00:26:51,119 --> 00:26:53,610
[ Huffing ]

260
00:26:54,689 --> 00:26:57,988
That's it, man.
Keep your legs moving.

261
00:26:59,294 --> 00:27:02,525
- Your father's a boxer too, isn't he ?
- Aye.

262
00:27:02,597 --> 00:27:05,998
- [ Huffing Continues ]
- Get your balance right.
Move your head.

263
00:27:07,068 --> 00:27:09,662
Lift those punches.

264
00:27:09,738 --> 00:27:12,172
That's it.
And again. And again.

265
00:27:13,642 --> 00:27:15,576
That's it.

266
00:27:16,845 --> 00:27:19,279
That's it ! Good man.

267
00:27:27,889 --> 00:27:29,823
Hey.

268
00:27:31,559 --> 00:27:34,255
I see you've put up
the ring.

269
00:27:34,329 --> 00:27:36,763
- Aye.
- Looks great.

270
00:27:47,409 --> 00:27:50,901
Well, sweetheart,

271
00:27:54,716 --> 00:27:58,345
did you die just so Joe Hamill
could sell us out ?

272
00:27:58,420 --> 00:28:00,354
- Hmm ?
- Hmm ?

273
00:28:01,489 --> 00:28:03,423
Nothin'.

274
00:28:04,926 --> 00:28:06,860
Just talkin' to myself.

275
00:28:06,928 --> 00:28:09,863
[ Bell Tolling ]

276
00:28:12,867 --> 00:28:16,769
12:00 noon.
Peace in Ireland.

277
00:28:16,838 --> 00:28:19,329
- [ Car Horns Honking ]
- [ Shouting, Chattering ]

278
00:28:19,407 --> 00:28:22,342
- [ Honking, Shouting Continue ]
- [ Trash Can Lids Banging ]

279
00:28:25,413 --> 00:28:28,007
- Ma, it's the cease-fire !
- [ Newscaster ]
There are continuing scenes...

280
00:28:28,083 --> 00:28:30,244
- [ Bell Tolling ]
- of celebration on the streets
of West Belfast,

281
00:28:30,318 --> 00:28:33,515
as 12:00 noon brought the
long-awaited I.R.A. cease-fire.

282
00:28:33,588 --> 00:28:36,682
Protestant spokespersons
opposed immediate movement...

283
00:28:36,758 --> 00:28:38,692
on the release of prisoners.

284
00:28:42,530 --> 00:28:44,964
You get to know who
the troublemakers are quick enough.

285
00:28:45,033 --> 00:28:48,093
Just keep an eye
on the tables.

286
00:28:48,169 --> 00:28:50,433
No one comes into the city
center after dark,

287
00:28:50,505 --> 00:28:53,770
so you only have to work
till 6:00 or so.

288
00:28:53,842 --> 00:28:56,208
- You ever been to London ?
- Aye.

289
00:28:57,278 --> 00:29:00,213
I got a few contacts there.
Come on.

290
00:29:08,123 --> 00:29:11,092
lke, where's Danny ?

291
00:29:11,159 --> 00:29:13,593
He's in the kitchen.

292
00:29:17,565 --> 00:29:20,227
[ Utensil Tinkling ]

293
00:29:41,756 --> 00:29:43,986
What's goin' on, Danny ?

294
00:29:46,227 --> 00:29:48,161
What do you mean ?

295
00:29:51,466 --> 00:29:55,232
I haven't seen you
in 14 years,

296
00:29:55,303 --> 00:29:59,103
and now you're right
next door to me every day.

297
00:29:59,174 --> 00:30:04,510
And when I do see you,
all I get from you is the odd grunt.

298
00:30:04,579 --> 00:30:06,513
Do you not think
that's strange ?

299
00:30:15,490 --> 00:30:17,754
Aye, it is strange.

300
00:30:17,826 --> 00:30:20,260
Oh, forget it, Danny.

301
00:30:28,421 --> 00:30:30,855
[ Ike ]
Come on. Pick it up.

302
00:30:34,928 --> 00:30:37,362
That's it. Good man.

303
00:30:40,633 --> 00:30:42,828
And again.
Move him about.

304
00:30:42,902 --> 00:30:45,894
- [ Chattering ]
- Beautiful. And again.

305
00:30:45,972 --> 00:30:48,236
Get the punches in.
That's it.

306
00:30:48,308 --> 00:30:51,800
And again.
Keep your guard up, Danny !

307
00:30:52,879 --> 00:30:55,313
Danny, come on in.
Look at these.

308
00:30:59,753 --> 00:31:01,812
Look.

309
00:31:01,888 --> 00:31:03,822
There's Maclean.

310
00:31:13,099 --> 00:31:16,034
''Holy Family
Sweep the All lrelands.''

311
00:31:18,938 --> 00:31:23,398
[ Sighs ]
What a waste of life.

312
00:31:23,476 --> 00:31:28,413
Six of them dead. Why the hell
did you get mixed up with them ?

313
00:31:32,018 --> 00:31:35,010
The police were burning people
out of their homes, lke.

314
00:31:35,088 --> 00:31:37,249
Soldiers shootin' people
on the corner.

315
00:31:37,323 --> 00:31:40,258
Why the hell do you think
I got involved ?

316
00:31:40,326 --> 00:31:42,760
I don't know.

317
00:31:42,829 --> 00:31:44,763
What's in the cupboard ?

318
00:31:52,105 --> 00:31:56,371
- Ah, it's locked.
- We're lockin' up, lads.

319
00:31:56,443 --> 00:32:00,106
There's only odds and ends in there
belongin' to the community center.

320
00:32:23,169 --> 00:32:25,103
Fuckin' semtex.

321
00:32:34,914 --> 00:32:39,476
- [ Vehicles Approaching ]
- [ C.B. Radio, lndistinct ]

322
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:57,536
- [ Helicopter Whirring ]
- [ Train Whistle Blowing ]

323
00:33:23,897 --> 00:33:27,924
These are explosives, Birdy.
Why the fuck didn't you tell me
he was rootin' around in here ?

324
00:33:28,001 --> 00:33:30,435
Kept an eye on him.

325
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:43,114
The lock's broken.

326
00:33:48,154 --> 00:33:51,146
- It's gone.
- [ Floor Creaks ]

327
00:33:59,465 --> 00:34:01,695
Danny.

328
00:34:01,768 --> 00:34:04,202
Can I have
a word with you ?

329
00:34:18,885 --> 00:34:22,013
You're in trouble.
What did you do ?

330
00:34:26,292 --> 00:34:29,659
I found some stuff.
Semtex.

331
00:34:30,930 --> 00:34:33,831
Under the stage ?

332
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:35,834
[ Whispering ]
Bastards.

333
00:34:37,704 --> 00:34:40,935
- Well, where is it now ?
- In the river.

334
00:34:42,575 --> 00:34:45,237
Well, why didn't you give it
back to my father ?

335
00:34:46,346 --> 00:34:48,712
So they can kill more
innocent people ?

336
00:34:49,749 --> 00:34:51,717
What do you mean,
innocent people ?

337
00:34:52,785 --> 00:34:55,345
I mean
innocent people, Maggie.

338
00:34:57,557 --> 00:34:59,855
Do you want to get
yourself killed, Danny ?

339
00:35:00,927 --> 00:35:02,792
Not particularly.

340
00:35:04,497 --> 00:35:07,955
- Why did you really come back ?
- What do you mean ?

341
00:35:11,471 --> 00:35:14,406
I don't believe you just
came back here to box.

342
00:35:16,175 --> 00:35:18,302
If you ask me
to leave, I'll go.

343
00:35:18,378 --> 00:35:20,812
If I ask you to leave.

344
00:35:23,583 --> 00:35:27,144
Well, how far
can you go, Danny ?

345
00:35:27,220 --> 00:35:31,520
Turn around, start walking,
and when you've walked for 14 years,

346
00:35:31,591 --> 00:35:34,617
then stop and think
about what you did to me.

347
00:35:36,796 --> 00:35:38,923
I did it for ya.

348
00:35:41,234 --> 00:35:43,464
Oh, my God.

349
00:35:48,975 --> 00:35:50,909
[ Chuckles ]

350
00:35:51,978 --> 00:35:53,912
I'm sorry.

351
00:35:53,980 --> 00:35:56,414
[ Man On P.A. ]
The next train from platform one...

352
00:35:56,482 --> 00:35:59,815
will be the 10:50 service
to Londonderry--

353
00:35:59,886 --> 00:36:02,320
[ Continues, lndistinct ]

354
00:36:06,459 --> 00:36:08,689
I think we're
safe enough here.

355
00:36:08,761 --> 00:36:11,161
Ah, we're fine.
Don't worry about us.

356
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:13,164
Thank you.

357
00:36:27,580 --> 00:36:30,014
You used to talk to me,
Danny.

358
00:36:32,552 --> 00:36:37,512
You used to make me laugh.
Oh, go on, make me laugh.

359
00:36:40,226 --> 00:36:42,456
Am I not funny ?

360
00:36:42,528 --> 00:36:44,462
No.

361
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,734
[ Sighs ]

362
00:36:52,805 --> 00:36:55,365
Talk to me, Danny.

363
00:36:59,946 --> 00:37:02,176
[ Sighs ]

364
00:37:02,248 --> 00:37:04,478
Talk to you in my mind.

365
00:37:07,253 --> 00:37:09,187
What do you mean ?

366
00:37:16,028 --> 00:37:18,963
In prison, you get used
to silence, you know ?

367
00:37:24,804 --> 00:37:29,241
I mean, at first, you, you hold on
to all the old voices in your head--

368
00:37:31,144 --> 00:37:34,629
kids you knew at school,
old friends and such.

369
00:37:34,762 --> 00:37:39,222
Well, after a while,
those voices start to fade,

370
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:44,761
and you end up talkin' to yourself
for a bit of company, you know ?

371
00:37:48,142 --> 00:37:50,576
And then something
strange happens.

372
00:37:54,015 --> 00:37:58,179
It's as if even your own
voice doesn't belong there...

373
00:37:58,253 --> 00:38:00,448
in the silence.

374
00:38:00,521 --> 00:38:02,386
It's unwelcome.

375
00:38:07,161 --> 00:38:09,095
Go on, Danny.

376
00:38:09,163 --> 00:38:12,291
[ Sighs ]
Well, in the end,

377
00:38:12,367 --> 00:38:15,302
it's the silence
becomes your best friend.

378
00:38:20,541 --> 00:38:23,476
And in the quiet,
a face will come to you, and,

379
00:38:25,647 --> 00:38:31,108
and you talk to that person
without sayin' anything, and--

380
00:38:34,856 --> 00:38:38,519
[ Sighs ]
Gee, I'm not makin' any sense.

381
00:38:38,593 --> 00:38:41,494
Never make
any fuckin' sense.

382
00:38:43,164 --> 00:38:45,598
What are you sayin', Danny ?

383
00:38:48,303 --> 00:38:52,239
I've lived with your face
in silence for 14 years, Maggie.

384
00:38:53,508 --> 00:38:57,000
You know, it's hard
to talk to the real you.

385
00:38:59,180 --> 00:39:02,479
I'm not who I was.

386
00:39:06,921 --> 00:39:09,685
Try the elbow.
Set down on the way. That's it.

387
00:39:09,757 --> 00:39:12,783
Once more. That's it.
Snap on your jab.

388
00:39:12,860 --> 00:39:15,420
That's it. One more.

389
00:39:15,496 --> 00:39:17,987
Come on. One-two !
And again.

390
00:39:18,066 --> 00:39:20,694
- [ lke ] And again.
- He wants to join.

391
00:39:22,870 --> 00:39:24,804
He's the boss.

392
00:39:24,872 --> 00:39:26,806
- One-two.
- Ike !

393
00:39:28,576 --> 00:39:31,306
- Shadowbox.
- He wants to join.

394
00:39:31,379 --> 00:39:33,813
Use the rest
of the ring, now.

395
00:39:37,251 --> 00:39:39,185
Come here.

396
00:39:45,460 --> 00:39:48,896
- No way, missus.
- Who are you to talk, lke Weir ?

397
00:39:53,067 --> 00:39:55,262
Make him have
a blood test.

398
00:39:55,336 --> 00:39:58,032
If he's clear and
he stays off the junk,

399
00:39:58,106 --> 00:40:00,040
he can join.

400
00:40:01,309 --> 00:40:03,834
[ Danny ]
Keep your head movin' now.

401
00:40:03,911 --> 00:40:05,845
That's it.
Duck and weave.

402
00:40:05,913 --> 00:40:07,847
Bob and weave.

403
00:40:11,386 --> 00:40:14,685
- Well done.
- [ Chattering ]

404
00:40:14,756 --> 00:40:16,690
Keep on the move.
That's it.

405
00:40:16,758 --> 00:40:21,024
Come on. Hold on. Thumbs out.
That's it. Elbows in. Nice and tight.

406
00:40:21,095 --> 00:40:23,029
Good. Very good.

407
00:40:24,799 --> 00:40:27,597
Danny. Look at these.

408
00:40:29,737 --> 00:40:33,673
Headgear's gone.
You can't spar with these.

409
00:40:34,776 --> 00:40:36,710
Look at that.

410
00:40:36,778 --> 00:40:38,769
- [ Sean ] And he didn't do it ?
- [ Chattering ]

411
00:40:38,846 --> 00:40:40,780
[ Harry ]
Shh, shh, shh !

412
00:40:43,718 --> 00:40:47,119
- What does that mean, Bootsy ?
- What ?

413
00:40:47,188 --> 00:40:50,021
''Nonsectarian.''

414
00:40:51,826 --> 00:40:53,760
Catholics
and Protestants together.

415
00:40:57,065 --> 00:41:00,228
What about the Jews, Bootsy ?
And the Arabs ?

416
00:41:01,636 --> 00:41:03,501
And the Muslims ?

417
00:41:03,571 --> 00:41:05,869
l suppose they can come too,
if they want.

418
00:41:12,947 --> 00:41:16,474
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

419
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:22,045
Liam, move in !

420
00:41:23,891 --> 00:41:26,382
- Come on !
- [ Cheering, Shouting Continue ]

421
00:41:28,463 --> 00:41:31,830
Holy Family's
always been nonsectarian.

422
00:41:31,899 --> 00:41:34,390
Protestants
and Catholics together.

423
00:41:34,469 --> 00:41:36,903
- Write that down !
- [ Bell Dings ]

424
00:41:46,881 --> 00:41:48,906
And the winner is...

425
00:41:48,983 --> 00:41:51,110
in the red corner:

426
00:41:51,185 --> 00:41:53,949
Doyle from
the Holy Family Club,

427
00:41:54,021 --> 00:41:56,512
Belfast.

428
00:41:56,591 --> 00:41:59,321
I won !

429
00:41:59,393 --> 00:42:01,327
You fought
a great fight.

430
00:42:03,731 --> 00:42:05,665
Okay, Danny. Let's go.

431
00:42:05,733 --> 00:42:07,758
Don't forget. It's your
