485
00:45:55,420 --> 00:45:57,786
You're not ready.

486
00:45:57,856 --> 00:46:01,883
- Have you had enough, son ?
- I'll tell you when l've had enough.

487
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:04,394
- [ Bell Dings ]
- Finish him.

488
00:46:04,462 --> 00:46:06,396
[ Man ]
Danny !

489
00:46:11,403 --> 00:46:14,031
[ Man ]
Get him down, Danny !

490
00:46:20,078 --> 00:46:22,569
Go on, Danny !

491
00:46:22,647 --> 00:46:24,706
[ Woman ]
Go on, Danny !

492
00:46:24,783 --> 00:46:26,876
Get off the ropes !

493
00:46:29,287 --> 00:46:31,687
- Go on, Danny !
- [ Groans ]

494
00:46:33,425 --> 00:46:36,360
- Are you okay ? Can you continue ?
- Yes.

495
00:46:36,428 --> 00:46:38,828
- Go on, Danny ! Get him !
- Go on !

496
00:46:38,897 --> 00:46:41,365
[ Man ]
Come on !

497
00:46:44,903 --> 00:46:48,339
He can't put him down !
He fuckin' won't bow down !

498
00:46:51,276 --> 00:46:53,244
Hold him, Danny !

499
00:46:53,311 --> 00:46:55,506
[ Man ]
Come on, Danny ! Come on !

500
00:46:55,580 --> 00:46:58,208
Stay on your feet, lad !
Stay on your feet !

501
00:47:02,253 --> 00:47:05,654
[ Ike ] Don't go down !
Stay on your feet, Danny !

502
00:47:05,723 --> 00:47:08,157
[ Man ]
Twenty seconds !

503
00:47:08,226 --> 00:47:10,353
[ Ike ]
Stay on your feet, Danny !

504
00:47:10,428 --> 00:47:12,362
[ Bell Dings ]

505
00:47:26,778 --> 00:47:29,576
He doesn't look
much like a quitter to me.

506
00:47:29,647 --> 00:47:32,582
[ Crowd Chanting ]
Danny ! Danny ! Danny !

507
00:47:32,650 --> 00:47:36,882
Danny ! Danny ! Danny !

508
00:47:51,536 --> 00:47:54,266
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

509
00:48:00,378 --> 00:48:02,778
What was that about, scrapper ?

510
00:48:04,449 --> 00:48:08,408
- What do you mean ?
- Those were powerful emotions
you stirred up tonight.

511
00:48:10,321 --> 00:48:14,985
- What are you up to ?
- I was just boxin'.

512
00:48:16,361 --> 00:48:19,592
It's not just boxin', Danny.
It's a fuckin' statement--

513
00:48:19,664 --> 00:48:21,757
standin' there
gettin' your head knocked off.

514
00:48:24,736 --> 00:48:26,601
What was that about ?

515
00:48:31,342 --> 00:48:33,708
I want the stuff back,
scrapper.

516
00:48:37,315 --> 00:48:40,250
What stuff ?

517
00:48:40,318 --> 00:48:44,721
[ Chuckles ] All right, Danny.
Play it whatever way you want.

518
00:48:46,524 --> 00:48:50,016
Fourteen years wasn't enough
to teach you, then. Was it, now ?

519
00:48:52,430 --> 00:48:55,160
- What'd he want ?
- Nothin', lke.

520
00:48:57,268 --> 00:48:59,202
Good.

521
00:49:01,039 --> 00:49:03,530
He ruined
your life once already.

522
00:49:03,608 --> 00:49:06,076
- Don't give him a second chance.
- I won't.

523
00:49:10,748 --> 00:49:13,683
You should have put him away
the first time.

524
00:49:13,751 --> 00:49:18,313
You did him a favor.
He'll never forgive you for it.

525
00:49:19,991 --> 00:49:21,925
[ Guard ]
I.D., please.

526
00:49:21,993 --> 00:49:23,927
I.D. ?

527
00:49:27,198 --> 00:49:29,132
Thank you.

528
00:49:42,247 --> 00:49:44,272
I'm not too sure
about this, Maggie.

529
00:49:44,349 --> 00:49:47,045
Well, it's safer than being
seen together in West Belfast.

530
00:49:53,992 --> 00:49:56,552
Why didn't you ask me
to wait ?

531
00:49:59,097 --> 00:50:02,396
- I would have waited.
- Don't be sayin' that.
Fourteen years, Maggie.

532
00:50:02,467 --> 00:50:05,493
- I would have waited.
- You were only 16.

533
00:50:05,570 --> 00:50:11,133
- Did you not trust me ?
- How the hell could I ?
I was mad in love with ya.

534
00:50:11,209 --> 00:50:14,736
And I wanted
to keep it that way.

535
00:50:14,812 --> 00:50:17,781
Not have it eaten up
day by day.

536
00:50:17,849 --> 00:50:21,945
So you made the decision
for both of us ?

537
00:50:22,020 --> 00:50:24,921
- You made your own
decisions too, Maggie.
- What do you mean ?

538
00:50:24,989 --> 00:50:27,617
You married my best friend,
for God's sake.

539
00:50:28,993 --> 00:50:32,326
Well, did you expect me
to remain faithful to you ?

540
00:50:33,598 --> 00:50:37,625
I suppose I did.
I thought I was bein' romantic.

541
00:50:37,702 --> 00:50:40,933
Mmm. Givin' you
your freedom or somethin'.

542
00:50:41,005 --> 00:50:44,600
You were giving me my freedom, but you
wanted me to stay faithful to you ?

543
00:50:44,676 --> 00:50:47,406
I was only 19.

544
00:50:47,478 --> 00:50:49,412
[ Maggie ]
Mm-hmm.

545
00:50:50,882 --> 00:50:52,816
- Shake my hand.
- What ?

546
00:50:52,884 --> 00:50:56,081
Shake my hand, Danny Boy Flynn.
Billy Patterson, bantamweight.

547
00:50:56,154 --> 00:50:58,748
- Jesus, Billy ! How are you doin' ?
- Good, good.

548
00:50:58,823 --> 00:51:01,348
I'm doin' fine.
Don't look now.

549
00:51:01,426 --> 00:51:03,360
But there's a car
behind ya,

550
00:51:03,428 --> 00:51:07,694
and the last Catholic boy who was
in that car didn't die a happy death.

551
00:51:07,765 --> 00:51:10,962
- So I'll walk you
to the peace line together.
- Let's go.

552
00:51:11,035 --> 00:51:12,969
[ Car Engine Revving ]

553
00:51:19,110 --> 00:51:22,876
Bye-bye, Maggie.
Good luck, Danny.

554
00:51:22,947 --> 00:51:25,472
- Stop by and do
a bit of training sometime.
- Will do.

555
00:51:27,352 --> 00:51:30,287
[ Children Chattering ]

556
00:51:39,931 --> 00:51:42,695
[ Children Chattering ]

557
00:51:42,767 --> 00:51:45,395
- What's wrong ?
- I don't take gear from cops.

558
00:51:45,470 --> 00:51:48,530
- Why ?
- 'Cause they won't let
my dad out of prison.

559
00:51:48,606 --> 00:51:51,131
- Yeah, go on !
- [ Man ] That's great, Reggie.

560
00:51:57,281 --> 00:51:59,715
What about you, Liam ?

561
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:18,901
[ Child Chattering ]

562
00:52:18,970 --> 00:52:20,995
[ Man ] Come on, lads.
Come on. Photograph time.

563
00:52:21,072 --> 00:52:25,372
- What's all this ?
- It's a gift.

564
00:52:28,112 --> 00:52:31,138
- A gift from who ?
- Community relations.

565
00:52:33,418 --> 00:52:35,352
- All right.
- Come here.

566
00:52:36,554 --> 00:52:39,079
Group together like that.

567
00:52:45,163 --> 00:52:48,997
- Community relations ?
- Aye. Reggie Bell.

568
00:52:49,067 --> 00:52:53,766
This stuff is from the cops,
lke, and we can't accept it.

569
00:52:56,474 --> 00:53:00,410
Listen, these kids have barely
got shoes on their feet.

570
00:53:00,478 --> 00:53:03,106
Some of them
come here in rags.

571
00:53:03,181 --> 00:53:06,014
Look at them now.
They look great.

572
00:53:06,084 --> 00:53:09,576
Now I don't give a fuckin' shite
who these togs come from.
They're on their backs.

573
00:53:09,654 --> 00:53:12,282
- All right.
- They're not comin' off.

574
00:53:12,357 --> 00:53:16,623
We simply can't negotiate until
the terrorists lay down their arms.

575
00:53:16,694 --> 00:53:21,722
The police are Protestant.
They're not welcome in Catholic areas.

576
00:53:21,799 --> 00:53:25,701
ln contrast, it seems the whole
of Belfast, Catholic and Protestant,

577
00:53:25,770 --> 00:53:30,639
is welcome at the recently reopened,
nonsectarian Holy Family Boxing Club.

578
00:53:30,708 --> 00:53:33,643
- Takin' gear from the cops.
- The boys from the club...

579
00:53:33,711 --> 00:53:36,475
recently received
a generous donation of equipment.

580
00:53:36,547 --> 00:53:39,015
And Danny Flynn,
who fights out of Holy Family,

581
00:53:39,083 --> 00:53:43,042
has signed up for a rematch
with Eddie Carroll at the city center.

582
00:53:53,531 --> 00:53:56,398
[ Machine Gunfire, Gunshots ]

583
00:53:56,467 --> 00:53:59,732
[ Men Shouting ]

584
00:53:59,804 --> 00:54:02,739
[ Shouting Continues ]

585
00:54:04,976 --> 00:54:07,911
[ Trash Can Lid Banging ]

586
00:54:19,424 --> 00:54:22,621
- [ Banging Continues ]
- [ Helicopter Whirring ]

587
00:54:24,829 --> 00:54:27,593
[ Whirring Continues ]

588
00:54:27,665 --> 00:54:30,600
- [ Shouting ]
- [ Sirens Wailing ]

589
00:54:30,668 --> 00:54:32,602
[ Wailing Continues ]

590
00:54:36,374 --> 00:54:39,002
[ Officer ] Get them !
Get those sons of bitches !

591
00:54:39,077 --> 00:54:41,341
[ Shouting Continues ]

592
00:54:44,849 --> 00:54:47,249
[ Helicopter Whirring ]

593
00:54:48,419 --> 00:54:51,479
Who fired at Danny Flynn
last night, Harry ?

594
00:54:51,556 --> 00:54:53,956
I don't know.
My units shoot to kill.

595
00:54:54,025 --> 00:54:56,220
You're in charge
of the district.

596
00:54:56,294 --> 00:54:58,228
No.

597
00:54:58,296 --> 00:55:01,231
I report to you.
Did you see this ?

598
00:55:04,669 --> 00:55:07,399
He's fillin' people's heads
full of shit, Joe.

599
00:55:07,472 --> 00:55:09,997
''Leave the fighting to Danny'' means
that all the people who are in prison,

600
00:55:10,074 --> 00:55:12,770
who died, who didn't
surrender to the Brits--

601
00:55:12,844 --> 00:55:17,076
that means that their sacrifices aren't
worth a lousy fuckin' boxin' match.

602
00:55:17,148 --> 00:55:19,946
He's spreadin' dissent, Joe.

603
00:55:20,017 --> 00:55:23,578
Maybe you're the one who's
spreadin' dissent, Harry.

604
00:55:28,159 --> 00:55:32,220
I'm trying to hold it together
in a district full of junkies,
thieves and losers,

605
00:55:32,296 --> 00:55:34,764
while all he's trying to say is
that everything will be all right...

606
00:55:34,832 --> 00:55:38,563
if the Catholics and Protestants
will hold hands together.

607
00:55:39,637 --> 00:55:42,504
It's shit, isn't it, Joe ?

608
00:55:42,573 --> 00:55:46,065
ls it, Harry ?

609
00:55:46,144 --> 00:55:48,078
Shit ?

610
00:55:48,146 --> 00:55:50,546
You know we're gonna have
to live with them sometime.

611
00:55:50,615 --> 00:55:53,880
- Who's ''them'' ?
- The Protestants, Harry.

612
00:55:53,951 --> 00:55:56,215
The other half
of the population.

613
00:56:01,092 --> 00:56:05,461
You're never going to be
treated as an equal, Joe.

614
00:56:05,530 --> 00:56:08,465
Not if we keep
bombin' 'em, no.

615
00:56:08,533 --> 00:56:11,127
I don't see any P.O.W.s
comin' home, Joe.

616
00:56:11,202 --> 00:56:15,696
Well, last night
didn't help, Harry.

617
00:56:15,773 --> 00:56:18,640
It didn't help at all.

618
00:56:18,709 --> 00:56:21,735
[ Man #1 ]
Keep it goin', Bootsy. Keep it goin'.

619
00:56:21,813 --> 00:56:23,747
And again.

620
00:56:23,815 --> 00:56:26,545
- [ Ike ]
Throw your combinations, Danny !
- And again.

621
00:56:26,617 --> 00:56:28,710
Let's go.
And again.

622
00:56:28,786 --> 00:56:30,583
[ Man #2 ]
One-two !

623
00:56:30,655 --> 00:56:32,816
- [ Ike ] Use the jab !
- Watch it !

624
00:56:32,890 --> 00:56:35,222
- Danny.
- [ lke ] Come on ! Again !

625
00:56:40,698 --> 00:56:43,531
That was a warning shot
they fired at you.

626
00:56:43,601 --> 00:56:45,660
- I'll see you later.
- Aye.

627
00:57:04,188 --> 00:57:07,123
You know, we can't keep doin'
what we're doin', Maggie.

628
00:57:10,361 --> 00:57:12,591
What are we doing ?

629
00:57:13,865 --> 00:57:17,301
[ Chuckles ]
You know what I'm sayin'. Come on.

630
00:57:18,803 --> 00:57:22,603
Yeah.
You're right.

631
00:57:34,752 --> 00:57:36,686
Give us a hug.

632
00:57:44,595 --> 00:57:47,029
You're a dangerous
fuckin' woman.

633
00:58:15,493 --> 00:58:18,929
You talked about voices in your head.
I couldn't stop them.

634
00:58:18,996 --> 00:58:22,864
I thought my head
would burst.

635
00:58:22,934 --> 00:58:26,563
And the only thing
that kept me sane--

636
00:58:28,139 --> 00:58:30,630
- Ah, it doesn't matter now.
- Go on. I'm listening.

637
00:58:30,708 --> 00:58:33,142
- It's not fair.
- Just finish it up, Maggie.

638
00:58:33,210 --> 00:58:37,840
[ Sighs ] It was the sound
of your voice saying,

639
00:58:39,917 --> 00:58:42,385
''Everything's gonna
be all right.''

640
00:58:43,454 --> 00:58:46,480
Geez, I never said that.

641
00:58:47,558 --> 00:58:51,050
Over and over again
in my head.

642
00:58:52,129 --> 00:58:54,563
''Everything is gonna
be all right.''

643
00:59:12,717 --> 00:59:16,813
Well, this is, this is okay.
This is, this is all right.

644
00:59:17,888 --> 00:59:21,483
What ?
What is this ?

645
00:59:24,528 --> 00:59:28,931
This is us.
You don't put a name on it.

646
00:59:55,924 --> 00:59:58,859
- Who is it ?
- It's Danny. Can I come in ?

647
01:00:01,897 --> 01:00:04,832
It's very late, Danny.

648
01:00:04,900 --> 01:00:08,301
- You shouldn't be here. It's not safe.
- I know.

649
01:00:14,410 --> 01:00:17,345
This is fuckin' ridiculous,
you know ?

650
01:00:27,956 --> 01:00:32,552
All this talk, Maggie, you know ?
We're kiddin' ourselves.

651
01:00:32,628 --> 01:00:34,619
I love you.

652
01:00:35,798 --> 01:00:38,596
There's nothin' else to say.

653
01:00:40,436 --> 01:00:42,427
We're not kids anymore, Danny.

654
01:00:42,504 --> 01:00:44,472
Yeah, we are.

655
01:00:48,343 --> 01:00:50,208
You're so fuckin' beautiful.

656
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:56,148
For 14 years
I was locked up.

657
01:00:56,218 --> 01:00:59,949
Well, my feelings were
locked up inside of me.

658
01:01:04,827 --> 01:01:06,761
And when I got
in the ring again,

659
01:01:06,829 --> 01:01:09,593
you can't imagine the relief
it was to feel the pain--

660
01:01:10,766 --> 01:01:13,530
to be back
in the world again.

661
01:01:13,602 --> 01:01:17,595
I can give you up in my head,
but my body's cryin' out for you.

662
01:01:20,042 --> 01:01:21,976
Don't.

663
01:01:32,421 --> 01:01:34,514
Be with me.

664
01:01:35,591 --> 01:01:37,525
No.

665
01:01:37,593 --> 01:01:40,255
Be with me.

666
01:01:42,397 --> 01:01:44,831
I'm going mad, Danny.

667
01:01:46,135 --> 01:01:49,901
I have a scream inside of me
day and night.

668
01:01:49,972 --> 01:01:53,237
Liam's upstairs.

669
01:01:58,514 --> 01:02:00,880
Have I said too much ?

670
01:02:00,949 --> 01:02:03,247
No.

671
01:02:03,318 --> 01:02:05,582
No.

672
01:02:07,990 --> 01:02:09,958
But...

673
01:02:11,593 --> 01:02:14,460
I think you've said
enough for now.

674
01:02:19,168 --> 01:02:22,160
- I think you'd better go.
- Okay.

675
01:02:42,925 --> 01:02:44,984
Is my da comin' home
or not ?

676
01:02:45,060 --> 01:02:47,893
Don't build up
your hopes, Liam.

677
01:02:47,963 --> 01:02:50,659
You said the prisoners
were comin' home.

678
01:02:58,273 --> 01:03:00,673
[ Door Closes ]

679
01:03:01,877 --> 01:03:04,368
What's wrong ?

680
01:03:05,814 --> 01:03:08,806
We're this close to a deal,

681
01:03:08,884 --> 01:03:11,819
but I'm gettin' no concessions
on the prisoners.

682
01:03:13,222 --> 01:03:16,385
It's as though the Brits
want the cease-fire to fail.

683
01:03:18,193 --> 01:03:21,185
Harry says the only thing
they respond to is violence.

684
01:03:27,436 --> 01:03:31,304
♪♪ [ Band Playing ]

685
01:03:31,373 --> 01:03:33,807
- It's a sellout.
- [ Man ] Go on, Belfast !

686
01:03:33,876 --> 01:03:36,970
Belfast is comin'
back to life.

687
01:03:37,045 --> 01:03:40,742
People see this man, who was
once committed to violence,

688
01:03:40,816 --> 01:03:42,977
now fightin'
within the rules.

689
01:03:43,051 --> 01:03:44,985
lt's caught
their imagination.

690
01:03:45,053 --> 01:03:48,545
People are here together--
Catholic and Protestant--

691
01:03:48,624 --> 01:03:50,489
with no animosity.

692
01:03:50,559 --> 01:03:52,993
[ Ike ]
Don't be overeager.

693
01:03:53,061 --> 01:03:55,495
If you go for him too early,
you're in trouble.

694
01:03:55,564 --> 01:03:57,759
- Ike.
- Reg.

695
01:03:57,833 --> 01:03:59,767
- How's it goin' ?
- Not bad.

696
01:03:59,835 --> 01:04:01,826
- Kids enjoyin' the gear ?
- Just great.

697
01:04:01,904 --> 01:04:05,635
[ Matt ] You know Reggie Bell,
R.U.C. community relations.

698
01:04:05,707 --> 01:04:08,938
Good luck tonight.
lt's great for the city.

699
01:04:09,011 --> 01:04:11,138
Great for all of us.

700
01:04:13,215 --> 01:04:15,376
Lovely.
I'll leave you two.

701
01:04:15,450 --> 01:04:17,884
- All the best, Reg.
- Thanks.

702
01:04:22,524 --> 01:04:24,958
- l don't like bein' used.
- [ Matt ] What's wrong ?

703
01:04:25,027 --> 01:04:28,224
- I don't like bein' used.
- He gave the kids all the equipment.

704
01:04:28,297 --> 01:04:30,390
[ Ike ]
Concentrate on the boxin'.

705
01:04:30,465 --> 01:04:33,866
♪♪ [ Band Playing ]

706
01:04:33,936 --> 01:04:37,235
[ Applause ]

707
01:04:40,642 --> 01:04:43,406
- Everything's set up.
- Okay.

708
01:04:43,478 --> 01:04:45,412
Here comes Joe Hamill.

709
01:04:45,480 --> 01:04:47,710
[ Applause ]

710
01:04:47,783 --> 01:04:50,115
[ Man ]
I.R.A. bastard !

711
01:04:50,185 --> 01:04:51,743
[ Booing ]

712
01:04:51,820 --> 01:04:54,584
[ Heckling ]

713
01:04:54,656 --> 01:04:56,886
- Bastard !
- Get out of Belfast !

714
01:04:56,959 --> 01:04:59,951
[ Announcer ]
Stop fighting amongst yourselves !

715
01:05:00,028 --> 01:05:02,428
Can we all sing together...

716
01:05:02,497 --> 01:05:05,898
a song we all know,
''Danny Boy'' ?

717
01:05:05,968 --> 01:05:08,562
- Where's Liam ?
- He's not comin'.

718
01:05:10,706 --> 01:05:12,697
Did he say
he didn't want to come ?

719
01:05:12,774 --> 01:05:15,265
That's right.
He said he didn't want to come.

720
01:05:20,182 --> 01:05:23,015
♪ Oh, Danny boy ♪

721
01:05:23,085 --> 01:05:26,782
♪ The pipes
The pipes are callin' ♪

